# Parameter R/W Migration — Walkthrough

## Changes Made

### [laser_controller_page.py](file:///Users/simone/Desktop/Università/Trento/Master_theses/RP_Spectroscopy/GUI_TEST/gui/laser_controller_page.py)

**[ParametersPage](file:///Users/simone/Desktop/Universit%C3%A0/Trento/Master_theses/RP_Spectroscopy/GUI_TEST/gui/laser_controller_page.py#94-232) class** — Decoupled from hardware layer:

- Added `sig_parameter_changed = Signal(str, object)` — emitted when user edits a value
- [load_parameters()](file:///Users/simone/Desktop/Universit%C3%A0/Trento/Master_theses/RP_Spectroscopy/GUI_TEST/gui/laser_controller_page.py#141-183) now accepts a plain dict from YAML (with `writeable_parameters` key) instead of [WriteableParameter](file:///Users/simone/Desktop/Universit%C3%A0/Trento/Master_theses/RP_Spectroscopy/GUI_TEST/libraries/interface.py#149-192) objects
- [on_cell_changed()](file:///Users/simone/Desktop/Universit%C3%A0/Trento/Master_theses/RP_Spectroscopy/GUI_TEST/gui/laser_controller_page.py#185-217) emits `sig_parameter_changed` instead of calling `param.set_value()` directly

