### [general_manager.py](file:///Users/simone/Desktop/Università/Trento/Master_theses/RP_Spectroscopy/GUI_TEST/libraries/general_manager.py)

**Signal wiring** in [connect_to_board()](file:///Users/simone/Desktop/Universit%C3%A0/Trento/Master_theses/RP_Spectroscopy/GUI_TEST/libraries/general_manager.py#79-158):
- `sig_parameters_loaded` → [on_parameters_loaded](file:///Users/simone/Desktop/Universit%C3%A0/Trento/Master_theses/RP_Spectroscopy/GUI_TEST/libraries/general_manager.py#167-176) (stores + populates GUI) + `laser.load_parameters`
- `sig_parameter_changed` → `laser.set_parameter_value`
- Defaults button → `services.load_default_parameters(board)` (was `laser.restore_default_parameters`)
- Triggers `services.load_parameters(board)` alongside [load_advanced_settings](file:///Users/simone/Desktop/Universit%C3%A0/Trento/Master_theses/RP_Spectroscopy/GUI_TEST/libraries/service_manager.py#467-489)

**Simplified methods:**
- [on_laser_connected()](file:///Users/simone/Desktop/Universit%C3%A0/Trento/Master_theses/RP_Spectroscopy/GUI_TEST/libraries/general_manager.py#159-166) — no longer reaches into `interface.writeable_params`
- New [on_parameters_loaded(dict)](file:///Users/simone/Desktop/Universit%C3%A0/Trento/Master_theses/RP_Spectroscopy/GUI_TEST/libraries/general_manager.py#167-176) replaces old [on_parameters_updated()](file:///Users/simone/Desktop/Universit%C3%A0/Trento/Master_theses/RP_Spectroscopy/GUI_TEST/libraries/general_manager.py#164-176)
- [cleanup()](file:///Users/simone/Desktop/Universit%C3%A0/Trento/Master_theses/RP_Spectroscopy/GUI_TEST/libraries/general_manager.py#254-277) — uses `services.save_parameters()` directly instead of `QMetaObject.invokeMethod`

render_diffs(file:///Users/simone/Desktop/Università/Trento/Master_theses/RP_Spectroscopy/GUI_TEST/libraries/general_manager.py)

## Data Flow (Complete)

| Action | Flow |
|---|---|
| **Board connected** | GM calls `services.load_parameters(board)` → SM reads YAML → emits `sig_parameters_loaded(dict)` → GM stores + populates GUI, LM calls `interface.load_parameters_from_dict(dict)` |
| **User edits value** | ParametersPage emits `sig_parameter_changed(name, val)` → LM calls `interface.set_value(name, val)` |
| **Restore defaults** | GM calls `services.load_default_parameters(board)` → same flow as "Board connected" but from `_default.yaml` |
| **App closes** | GM collects values from LM → calls `services.save_parameters(board, values_dict)` → SM writes to YAML |

## Verification

> [!IMPORTANT]
> These changes require manual testing with the RedPitaya hardware. The recommended test flow:
> 1. Launch app, connect to a board → Parameters page should populate from YAML
> 2. Edit a parameter → check logs for forwarding to hardware
> 3. Click "Default settings" → table reloads from `_default.yaml`
> 4. Close app → verify `_parameters.yaml` has updated values
> 5. Relaunch → verify persisted values appear
